HOUSE BILL 2089
By Powers
SENATE BILL 2168
By Yager
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 15;
Title 49, Chapter 1 and Title 49, Chapter 6, relative
to victims of communism.
WHEREAS, over 100 years have passed since the Bolshevik Revolution in Russia and
the formation of the first communist government under Vladimir Lenin, which led to decades of
oppression and violence under communist regimes throughout the world; and
WHEREAS, based on the economic philosophies of Karl Marx, communism has proven
incompatible with the ideals of liberty, prosperity, and dignity of human life; and
WHEREAS, communism has given rise to infamous totalitarian dictators, including
Joseph Stalin, Vladimir Lenin, Mao Zedong, and Pol Pot; and
WHEREAS, communist regimes worldwide have killed more than 100 million people and
subjected countless others to exploitation and unspeakable atrocities, with victims representing
many different ethnicities, creeds, and backgrounds; and
WHEREAS, communist regimes have systematically robbed their own citizens of the
rights of freedom of worship, freedom of speech, and freedom of association through false
promises of equality and liberation or through coercion, brutality, and fear; and
WHEREAS, regimes persecuted those who spoke out in opposition and held many
victims of communism as political prisoners, while others were killed in genocidal, state-
sponsored purges of undesirable groups; and
WHEREAS, in addition to violating basic human rights, communist regimes have
suppressed intellectual freedom, cultural life, and self-determination movements in more than
forty nations; now, therefore,
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SB2168
010623
- 1 -

SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 49, Chapter 6, Part 10, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
(a) November 7 of each year, LEAs and public charter schools shall recognize
the day as "Victims of Communism Day" to honor victims of communist regimes.
(b) If an LEA or public charter school provides a world history and geography
course to high school students enrolled in an LEA or public charter school, then the LEA
or public charter school shall provide the students enrolled in the course with at least
forty-five (45) minutes of instruction on how victims suffered under communist regimes,
including through poverty, starvation, migration, systemized lethal violence, and
suppression of speech, in conjunction with any of the following topics:
(1) Mao Zedong and the Cultural Revolution;
(2) Joseph Stalin and the Soviet System;
(3) Fidel Castro and the Cuban Revolution;
(4) Pol Pot and the Khmer Rouge; or
(5) Nicolás Maduro and the Chavismo movement.
(c) If Victims of Communism Day is on a day that a high school student who is
enrolled in a world history and geography course does not receive instruction for the
course, then the student must receive the instruction required by this section on the next
day that the student receives instruction for the course.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it,
and applies to the 2026-2027 school year and subsequent school years.
